g.title: cleans the work directory. It lists the entries in the work directory and deletes all but hidden files, `.fusion.keep`, and `.fusion.log`, unless the `.fusion.keep` file exists. If there is a `.fusion.log` file, it renames it to `.fusion.<date>.log`, where <date> is the current date in the format `20060102.150405`. It logs an error if there is an issue while cleaning the work directory.

renames a file or directory from oldPath to newPath in a parallel fashion. It takes a context.Context object, the old path, the new path, and an errgroup.Group pointer that allows goroutines to be synchronized. It returns a fuse.Status value indicating the success or failure of the operation.
serves a FUSE file system at the given mount point. On shutdown it unmounts the file system and sets the exit code to zero. Returns the exit code.

returns a *fuse.Server and a fusion.Service. It builds a fusion filesystem and mounts it at the given mount point. It creates the data stores for S3, Google Cloud Storage, and Azure Cloud Storage, and then builds a global data store that forwards requests to the correct data store. It checks the data store connection before mounting, and then creates and mounts the fusion filesystem. Finally, it gives the fusion process more priority, cleans the work directory on spot terminations retries, and logs instance metadata when running on AWS EC2.
